Abstract: 
In this paper we provide an empirical investigation of the determinants of divorce in the
Danish marriage market. The paper complements Svarer (2002) in two ways. First, it
considers more carefully the potential endogeneity of premarital cohabitation in the divorce
equation. Second, it discusses more thouroghly the effects of other covariates on the divorce
hazard.
